summary: SummaryHighlightsClean IngredientsCruelty FreeVeganFinely fill and detail brows with the Morphe Nano Brow Pencil. This pin-thin, .9mm-tipped pencil applies tiny strokes that are so precise, no one will believe they aren't your natural brow hairs. The all-day formula goes on smoothly and blends with the spoolie to effortlessly enhance sparse areas.
details: DetailsFeatures.9mm-tipped retractable brow pencilSpoolie end to blendLongwearing*Water-, smudge-, transfer-, and fade-resistant**Based on a 33-person clinical study.Research Results100% agreed this pencil has the tiniest tip they've ever used.*97% agreed it provides the finest hairlike strokes.*100% agreed it effortlessly fills in sparse patches.*97% agreed it's sweat-, water-, smudge-, transfer-, and fade-resistant.**Based on 33-person clinical and consumer perception studies.Item 2644138How To UseTo prevent your ultraprecision pin-thin tip from breaking, twist it up until it's just visible.Use the spoolie to brush up your brows and reveal any sparse areas.Use the tip to fill in sparse areas with short, gentle, hairlike strokes.Use the spoolie to blend and shape your brows.IngredientsSynthetic Wax, C12-15 Alkyl Ethylhexanoate, Polyglyceryl-2 Triisostearate, Hydrogenated Coco-Glycerides, Mica, Euphorbia Cerifera (Candelilla) Wax (Candelilla Cera, Cire de candelilla), Copernicia Cerifera (Carnauba) Wax (Cera Carnauba, Cire de carnauba), Zinc Stearate, Triethoxycaprylylsilane, Sorbitan Tristearate, Phenoxyethanol, Tocopheryl Acetate, Ethylhexylglycerin, Glyceryl Caprylate. May Contain: Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891), Iron Oxides (CI 77491, CI 77492, CI 77499).

reviews.headline: Used one time and the pencil fell out
reviews.comments: I bought this and was excited to try it! I used to love Morphe's eyebrow pencils because they were affordable and good quality! However, this pencil was a waste of money. I used it once and the next day the pencil part flew out and broke.

reviews.headline: BREAKS SO EASILY!\
reviews.comments: literally can only ever use the tiniest bit at at a time but even then it breaks!

reviews.headline: SUPER Fine point, pigmented and easy to work with!
reviews.comments: Very glad I purchased this product from Ilta, it's reasonably priced and far exceeded my expectations. I recommend going to ilta and testing it on your hand to see for yourself the ease of making realistic looking fine lines to perfectly mimic natural eyebrow hair.

reviews.headline: Love how thin it is!
reviews.comments: Good formula, not too slippery or dry. I feel like I can go through this product quickly though since it's super thin. But it's great for creating those fine brow lines.

reviews.headline: Amazing product, color could be better
reviews.comments: I love this brow pencil, it glides on so easily.  The tip is so tiny, I can create the best natural hair strokes.  I've been using glossier brow pencil forever and loved it, but debating switching to this one permanently.  Not sure of other reviews, but mine never breaks off.  I only twist it a few millimeters so maybe that's why it never breaks?  My only problem with this pencil is the color.  The Chocolate Mousse says it's a soft black, but it's definitely a dark brown.  It's much warmer than the glossier soft black, which is actually a soft black.  I wish Morphe would make one that's darker and more neutral.  It's a little warm for me, but not a deal breaker.

reviews.headline: Has potential to be better!
reviews.comments: The product itself is really nice, creates smooths and fine lines to create your ideal brow shape. I love the natural finish it creates, and how easy it is to use. Unfortunately, it lasts no longer than a week and breaks even with a light hand making the product run out quicker. Not moneys worth as it does not last.

reviews.headline: Breaks so easy
reviews.comments: This was a huge waste of money, I wish I could get my $ back. If you try to apply enough pressure to actually draw any visible line, it just breaks.

reviews.headline: Skip It

reviews.headline: Constantly breaks. ￼
reviews.comments: I'm surprised this product has so many good reviews. It is extremely thin.. but the tip of the pencil breaks off every time I use it. I'm going to go through it in a week at this rate. Unsure if it's a cheap product, or just a poor weak design.

reviews.comments: I've used the Morphe micro brow pencil for years. I picked up the nano version immediately, but unfortunately, it breaks *every time* I use it.  While I love how fine the pencil is, I'll likely stick with the micro version.

reviews.comments: On the plus side it is truly precise; however for mature i.e. sparse brows the micro and or brow definer will still be my first choice.  As soon as I use this one up!

reviews.comments: I've always wanted to try to the Benefit micro eye brow pens. I'm aiming for the most natural eyebrows due to have sparse hair brows. Morphe was said to be a dupe version, but no its not! No matter how soft handed I try to draw on my eyebrows the tip always breaks! Its frustrating because I'm basically wasting product. I'm just going to have to invest on the Benefit one..

reviews.headline: Not Worth It
reviews.comments: OMG this breaks so easily! Incredibly frustrating because it's a waste of product. There's probably a reason other pencils don't go so small.

faceoff_positive.comments:
Morphe Micro Brow Pencil: Your Secret Weapon for Flawless Brows!
I've been on the hunt for the perfect brow product for what feels like forever, and I can confidently say that the Morphe Micro Brow Pencil has ended my search thanks to this complimentary trial. This little gem is an absolute game-changer, delivering natural-looking, perfectly defined brows with incredible ease.

First off, let's talk about the ultra-fine tip. This is where the magic truly happens! It allows for such precise application, letting you create incredibly realistic hair-like strokes. Whether you have sparse areas you want to fill in seamlessly or you're looking to define your arch with razor-sharp precision, this pencil handles it all. It's like having a tiny, artistic brush right in your hand.

The formula is another major win. It's a hard-wax formula, which might sound intimidating, but it's actually incredibly smooth-gliding. It applies effortlessly without any tugging or pulling on your delicate brow hairs, which is a huge relief. The pigment is rich but buildable, meaning you can go for a softer, more natural look or build up the intensity for a bolder brow, all without it looking harsh or drawn on. It blends like a dream, too!

And can we talk about the spoolie? It's perfectly sized and perfectly placed on the other end of the pencil. This dual-ended design is super convenient for brushing your brow hairs into place before application, and then seamlessly blending out the product for a truly polished and natural finish. It helps distribute the color evenly and softens any lines, making your brows look effortlessly groomed.

I also appreciate the range of shades available. Finding a perfect match can be tricky, but Morphe offers a variety of hues that cater to different hair colors, ensuring you can find your ideal shade to create the most natural look possible.

In terms of longevity, this pencil holds its own. My brows stay defined and in place throughout the day, even through a bit of sweat or humidity. There's no smudging or fading, which is exactly what you want in a brow product.

For its affordable price point, the quality and performance of the Morphe Micro Brow Pencil are truly exceptional. It rivals many high-end brow products I've tried, making it an incredible value.

If you're looking to achieve beautifully shaped, natural-looking brows with precision and ease, you absolutely need to try the Morphe Micro Brow Pencil. It's become an essential part of my daily makeup routine, and I highly recommend it!
faceoff_positive.headline: A Game Changer in My Routine

faceoff_negative.comments:
Irecently tried the Nano Brow Pencil in "Latte", and it has quickly become a staple in my makeup routine. The color is the perfect soft brown with neutral undertones—not too warm or ashy—making it ideal for creating natural-looking brows that don't look drawn on.

The tip is super fine, which makes it easy to mimic real brow hairs, and the formula glides on smoothly without tugging. It's not overly creamy, so it doesn't smear or fade throughout the day, but it's also not stiff or dry. I can get super precise definition, but still blend it out for a soft finish with the spoolie on the other end.

"Latte" is a great shade if you have light to medium brown hair or darker blondes who want soft definition without harsh lines. Bonus: it's smudge-resistant and held up great even on warm days.
